Question

 

How long should records on identification procedures carried out on customers be kept for?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Seven years after the designated service was last provided to the customer

Question

 

What must you do every time an identification procedure is carried out for a customer?

Your answer:

Correct answer: You must make a record of the procedure

Question

 

When must your organisation keep records about an international funds transfer?

Your answer:

Correct answer: When it is involved in the transfer with two or more other organisations

Question

 

What is a "nostro" or "vostro" account?

Your answer:

Correct answer: A deposit account that a bank holds at a foreign or correspondent bank for the purposes of international payments

Question

 

What of the following is NOT KYC information that you must collect in relation to individual customers?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Passport ID number

Question

 

After collecting KYC information about a company, what details must you verify?

Your answer:

Correct answer: All of the above

Question

 

Complete the sentence. Safe harbour procedures only apply to…

Your answer:

Correct answer: … low to medium-risk individual customers

Question

 

What should organisations do in relation to any safe harbour procedures they adopt?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Document them in the AML program

Question

 

Which of the following documents should NOT be used to verify a customer's date of birth in a safe harbour procedure?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Any printout of a passport

Question

 

If the customer is an individual, you can assume the customer and beneficial owner are the same person unless reasonable grounds exist to think otherwise. True or false?

Your answer:

Correct answer: True

Question

 

If the customer and beneficial owner are of medium or lower ML/TF risk, what kind of safe harbour procedure to identify them?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Both document-based or electronic- based procedures

Question

 

Fill in the blank. The KYC identification procedure is _____ a customer who is an Australian government entity.

Your answer:

Correct answer: … not required if your organisation has already collected and verified information about…

Question

 

What must you do in relation to a politically exposed person who is Australian and has a high ML/TF risk?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Acquire senior management approval before you establish or continue a business relationship with them

Question

 

An enhanced due diligence program is NOT necessary in which of the following situations?

Your answer:

Correct answer: When a designated service is provided with a low ML/TF risk

Question

 

Which of the following is part of ongoing due diligence?

Your answer:

Correct answer: All of the above
